HEADWORD: Leucosoid
<hw>Leu"co*soid</hw> <pr>(-soid)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>Leucosia</ets>, the typical genus (fr. Gr. <grk>leyko`s</grk>
white) + <ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Like or
pertaining to the <fam>Leucosoidea</fam>, a tribe of marine crabs
including the box crab or <gen>Calappa</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

